subSubSection.paragraph:
M. globifrons

was briefly described by Menzies (
1962
) and a redescription of this species is badly needed. Regarding, the specimens of 

M. tillerae

from the Magellan Strait, Winkler (
1994
) wrote “it seems that this species [

M. tillerae

] occurs in the Magellan Strait” and pointed out that the setae on the propodus and carpus of the pereopods II–VI are longer than those illustrated by Bowman & Schultz (
1974
). These, together with the fact that the 
type
locality of 

M. tillerae

is southern California, hints at the possibility of a misidentification of the Magellan specimens.
